{"legislative_session": "2025RS", "identifier": "HB800", "title": "AN ACT relating to fiscal impact statements.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["General Assembly", "Insurance, Health", "State Agencies"], "abstracts": [{"note": "Summary of Original Version", "abstract": "Amend KRS 6.948 to require the commissioner of the Department of Insurance to include in a health mandate fiscal impact statement and state employee health plan impact statement any documentation, studies, written opinions, calculations, and citations in support of his or her findings and conclusions; include in the statement an estimate of any potential future cost savings, including an explanation why the bill would or would not provide future cost savings; require the commissioner to certify that the information in the health mandate fiscal impact statement or state employee health plan impact statement is accurate; require the commissioner of the Department of Insurance to include in a federal cost defrayal fiscal analysis any documentation, studies, written opinions, calculations, and citations in support of his or her findings and conclusions; require certification by the commissioner that the information provided in the cost defrayal fiscal analysis is accurate."}], "other_titles": [], "other_identifiers": [], "actions": [{"description": "introduced in House", "date": "2025-02-19T05:00:00+00:00", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["introduction"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "to Committee on Committees (H)", "date": "2025-02-19T05:00:00+00:00", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["referral-committee"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "taken from Committee on Committees (H)", "date": "2025-02-25T05:00:00+00:00", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "1s